      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add configurable retry for LLM provider API calls",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds opt-in `retry` config to `models.providers.<name>` for retrying transient LLM provider failures (ECONNREFUSED, 429, 502/503/504, timeouts)\n- Reuses existing channel retry infrastructure (`retryAsync`, `RetryConfig`, `RetryConfigSchema`) — no new retry primitives\n- Client errors (400/401/403/404) fail immediately without retry\n- Backward compatible: no retry when config is omitted\n\n## Motivation\n\nSelf-hosted LLM backends (vLLM, Ollama, etc.) sometimes require scheduled restarts for maintenance. Without provider-level retry, all in-flight and new requests fail during the restart window. This change lets users configure retry to ride through transient outages:\n\n```json5\nmodels.providers.vllm.retry = {\n  attempts: 25,\n  minDelayMs: 5000,\n  maxDelayMs: 60000,\n  jitter: 0.15\n}\n```\n\nCloses #31104\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] 15 unit tests covering retry behavior, error classification, config overrides\n- [x] TypeScript clean (no new errors in changed files)\n- [x] No regressions in broader test suite (pre-existing failures unrelated to this change)\n- [x] Security scan: no secrets, personal info, or internal IPs in any changed file",
